        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>A <em>horn of blasting</em> is a bright brass trumpet. It can be played as an instrument, granting a +2 item bonus to your Performance check.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">A</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> When you activate the horn by blowing into it with destructive intent, you create a blast note targeting one creature or object within 30 feet. The blast deals [[/r 3d6]] sonic damage. (<span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"28\" data-pf2-traits=\"evocation,sonic\" data-pf2-label=\"Horn of Blasting DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Fortitude</span> save).</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">D</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You can blow even louder to create an intense blast wave in a 30-foot cone that deals [[/r 8d6]] sonic damage. Each creature attempts a <span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"28\" data-pf2-traits=\"evocation,sonic\" data-pf2-label=\"Horn of Blasting DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Fortitude</span> save with the following effects.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature takes no damage.<br /><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.<br /><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and is deafened for 2d6 rounds.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Automatically applied effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>+2 item bonus to your Performance checks</li>\n</ul>"
